cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

The paper deals with learning computational models of object transformations from time-lapse videos, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also explores the use of generative models, which falls under the scope of artificial intelligence (AI) and graphics (GR), making cs.AI and cs.GR likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper involves the generation of depictions of objects, which can be considered as a multimedia (MM) application, making cs.MM a possible sub-category.
